			<ns0:name>robe...@google.com</ns0:name><ns0:uri>/u/108771824208521698652/</ns0:uri></ns0:author><ns0:content type="html">Right now when the system fails, it's usually totally silent about why.
What we need is infrastructure so that we can consistently surface as much
detail as is available as to the cause to the failure, and that would also
support a little bit more robust detection of why a failure has occurred.

For any failure that's detected the end-user ought to be able to email us a
text string or error code from the error message that shows us exactly
where the failure happened. Ideally it will also tell the user as much as
it usefully can to help them help themselves.

